{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9443859\charrsid9443859 No.  And, in fact I got in on Modern Languages, but then began to read theology, and that\rquote 
s because I was having problems with my sexual identity \endash  like a lot of gay people in that period.  I found that very very difficult to accept, and had a kind of religious conversion.  And so I read theology for Part I, and then realised what I
 was using religion for - which was really to escape a personal problem.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid15222664   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9443859\charrsid9443859 So I wanted to switch, and I had to make a choice, and I was torn between archaeology and anth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
