 Colin Lacey, who later went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Sussex{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and a woman called Audrey Lambert.  Colin had chosen to work in a grammar school, boys\rquote 
 grammar school in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Salford{\*\xmlclose}; Audrey went to the girls\rquote  grammar school; so the question was, where would I go?  What would I study?  So I had to think about it.  And I thought, \'93
Oh, what on earth can I \'85\'94  So I first thought, \'93Well, I could study a kind of school like my own \endash  a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Direct{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
