, (LAUGHS) and went to see him, and he called the Head of this secondary modern school in a place called Ordsall, Ordsall Secondary Modern School for Boys. The Head was there, the Head was called Haggerston, some name like that, and he said, \'93You
\rquote ll have this man, Haggerston, in your school, won\rquote t you, Haggerston, have this man in your school to study the students?\'94  And then the Head said, \'93Oh yes.  Yes, of course\'94
.  So this must have been in the summer term, so I duly turned up on the next day, not having a clue what I was going to do.  And the Head said, \'93Well, what do you want to do?  I mean, you\rquote re here till the end of term\'94.  And I said, \'93I
