t believe this because some of them weren\rquote t terribly bright, but some were okay, and I realised I\rquote d taught them the wrong formula!  So I thought, \'93There\rquote s only one way out of this\'94
, otherwise you lose credibility. So I had to go and say, \'93Look, lads, I\rquote m very sorry, but I\rquote ve taught you the wrong formula.\'94 By which time I became an expert maths teacher, because anything I taught from then on, they said, \'93
