\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid13331801\charrsid13331801 David:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9443859\charrsid9443859 
Well, I suppose the technology was relatively new, wasn\rquote t it?  The tape-recorder?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid13331801\charrsid13331801 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9443859\charrsid9443859 Yes, it was.  Yes.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid13331801\charrsid13331801 David:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9443859\charrsid9443859 
And I say it was interesting that the Department never said, \'93Have you got a tape-recorder?\'94  But presumably the anthropologists had grown up that you sat and chat with the tribe, and then you went back to your tent, a
nd wrote it up.  To me, it was natural just to record, just to switch it on, because it was there.  It was a great clumsy thing that I had, and all that reel-to-reel stuff, it was pretty terrible!  And I had to buy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid5056258 a better mike, to make it work, b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid9443859\charrsid9443859 ut I\rquote ve 
used a tape-recorder ever since in everything I\rquote ve done, I\rquote ve used tape-recorders.  Even if I go to a session, if I\rquote m going to write up about education, I\rquote ll often go to a meeting and say, \'93Do you mind if I tape it?\'94
  So, to me, taping something is second nature, because if you want, authentically, what people have said, you\rquote ve got to go to the tape.  You don\rquote t remember well enough.  You just don\rquote t remember well enough.
\par 
