t have, in some ways, been further apart in the way they set about their work, and the kind of scale of what they were doing.  But I was able to teach them to my students in a way that brought them together, and said, \'93
You go to John Holt, and you see what it\rquote s like to be a child learning, and what is going wrong in our schools, and you go to Illich, and you see you might have to make institutional reform in order to get this right\'94
. Both of these guys were highly libertarian, were uneasy about the kind of compulsion of the total institution of the conventional school.
