25m. budget at my disposal \endash  it was a bit of a shock!  I\rquote d also never worked closely with politicians.  I\rquote d never worked in a big bureaucracy.  But, you know, it\rquote 
s the usual story in my life.  If something comes along and I thought, \'93Well, that looks a really interesting chance.  Can I really afford to miss that?\'94  And then you just throw yourself in and get on with it.  I mean, Tessa Blackstone had just bee
n appointed to a job in ILEA before she went off to be Master of Birkbeck, and I\rquote d known Tessa anyway, and I said, \'93Tessa, how is it?\'94  And she said, \'93You\rquote ll find one thing really really difficult\'94.  She said, \'93
You are going to have to make decisions on very little evidence, and the academic in you will say, \lquote I can\rquote t make that decision until I know some more\rquote \'94, and she said, \'93You won\rquote t be able to\'94
